{
  "texts": [
    "It starts with a CNN component consisting of convolutional layers, batch normalization, and max pooling to extract spatial features from images.",
    "Next, it incorporates recurrent layers (LSTM and GRU) within a time-distributed layer, allowing the model to learn sequential patterns from the extracted features.",
    "Finally, the model includes dense layers with dropout regularization for classification.",
    "This combination of CNN and RCNN components allows the model to effectively learn spatial and temporal features, making it suitable for tasks requiring capturing information from both dimensions.",
    "The model relies on a bidirectional sequential neural network and utilizes convolutional layers, LSTM, and GRU layers for image classification."
  ]
}